name: HANDMADE SOLID WHITE OAK PLINTH FOR GARRARD 301
description:
HAND-MADE SOLID WHITE OAK PLINTH, FOR USE WITH YOUR GARRARD 301 TRANSCRIPTION TURNTABLE

Without doubt the best way to mount a Garrard/ Thorens transcription turntable, guaranteeing rumble-free and fatigue-free listening.

•	Solid hardwood frame made in white oak, with a spar varnish and beeswax finish. Designed for easy maintenance, durability and beautiful natural sheen

•	Accurate mitre joints, biscuit-jointed for strength

•	Solid oak shelving, glued and screwed for strength

•	Rebated frame with solid 1-inch fibreboard base, finished in satin black, complete with cut outs for motor, mains and tone arm cable

•	Effective de-coupler system (originally recommended by Garrard, Thorens and EMT manuals) using high quality sorbothene pods 

•	Baltic birch ply motor board, uncut or pre-cut for your choice of 9/ 10/ 12 inch tone arm. Motor board has been diligently prepared with undercoat primer, followed by restoration quality spray paint (charcoal metallic) and lacquer finish, resulting in a smooth, high-quality gloss

•	Rubber p-clip mains harness and complimentary footers provided complete with fitting instructions

This plinth design is both a quality console for iconic idler wheel turntables, as well as a beautiful piece of furniture. Made from the best of materials, it is extremely sturdy, every part being hand-made with care. By working with and emphasizing such natural materials as white oak and Baltic birch plywood, each plinth is unique and requires at least 25 person-hours to complete. The simple lines of this console allow the visual beauty of your turntable and tone arm to be appreciated, unhindered in any way. 

This versatile plinth also allows for quick and easy set-up of your transcription turntable. Additional Garrard and Thorens motor boards are available separately and are interchangeable with the main hardwood frame. This allows you the freedom to mount alternative units should you wish. Full details are available on request.

Listening notes: playback is rumble-free and powerful, drawing the listener ‘into’ the playback. The use of de-coupling systems is a tried and tested mounting method of choice and has been central in the design of many professional turntables (e.g. springs by Garrard, rubber mushrooms by Thorens, and rubber corner de-couplers by EMT). Using this age-old method, musical and vocal reproduction is portrayed in a natural and vivid manner. Any ‘hardness’ or ‘flatness’ experienced during playback (sometimes attributed to high-mass designed plinths) will be absent.

Your new plinth will be expertly packaged with great care and attention, and can be shipped anywhere in the world. 

Thank you for looking, please do not hesitate to contact us with any of your queries.
